.SH NAME
of_reserved_mem_device_init_by_idx \- assign reserved memory region to given device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" of_reserved_mem_device_init_by_idx
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Pointer to the device to configure
.IP "np" 12
Pointer to the device_node with 'reserved-memory' property
.IP "idx" 12
Index of selected region
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function assigns respective DMA-mapping operations based on reserved
memory region specified by 'memory-region' property in \fInp\fP node to the \fIdev\fP
device. When driver needs to use more than one reserved memory region, it
should allocate child devices and initialize regions by name for each of
child device.

Returns error code or zero on success.
